  ],
  "description": "BREP (Boundary Representation) is the native Open CASCADE Technology (OCCT) geometry format for storing B-rep solid and surface models. BREP files start with the ASCII string 'CASCADE Topology V1, (c) Matra Datavision' or a similar cascade version header, followed by sections for topology (shapes, faces, edges, vertices) and geometry (surfaces, curves, points in 3D space). Open CASCADE is the open-source 3D modeling kernel used by FreeCAD, Salome, Code_Aster, and many scientific/engineering applications. The BREP format encodes the complete topological structure: TopoDS_Shape hierarchy (compound, compsolid, solid, shell, face, wire, edge, vertex) with geometric support (Geom_Surface: Plane, Cylinder, Cone, Sphere, Torus, BSplineSurface; Geom_Curve: Line, Circle, Ellipse, BSplineCurve). BREP is a text-based ASCII format with a specific section structure: 'CASCADE Topology V1' header, followed by numbered location records, shape records, and geometry records.",
  "category": "CAD",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "hex-editor",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "Open CASCADE BREP Format — OCCT Documentation",
      "TopoDS_Shape and BRep_Builder OCCT API"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://dev.opencascade.org/doc/overview/html/specification__brep_format.html",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_CASCADE_Technology",
      "https://www.freecad.org/"
    ]
  },
